Did you know I had my first work permit at two years old? It’s true! I started modeling at a very young age, and I enjoyed it so much. Modeling was an excellent way for me to experience working with artists who had a vision of what they wanted to create and very unique ways of achieving it. I can remember being on this shoot and having them say, “we’re going to put bows all over you!” 😂 I contemplate allowing my kids to get into modeling. What do you think? Should I do it? Let me know in the comments!
.
.
.
@ccaagency

You probably know that I was a childhood model, but did you know that my sister modeled too? I love that mom keeps these sweet memories displayed throughout her home. Of course, I’m a big fan of meaningful and custom artwork on the walls of a home. But, does it get any more sentimental than photos, personal mementos and accomplishments? I think not! They make excellent conversation pieces, and friends always learn a bit more about you when they come over! Try it in an area of your home and you’ll see what I mean!
.
.
.
.

Well, the locs (dreadlocks) are back! I love my curly hair, truly I do. But guys, the simplicity and convenience of wearing my hair in a protective style like this one, is hard to beat! I have more time in the day when my hair is styled this way, and with a schedule like mine? I’ll take all the extra minutes and hours I can get! Thank you @ebonyrootshair for always making me feel and look like a million bucks! Ladies, what kinds of “beauty hacks” do you use to help make life a little easier here and there?

Yes, I’m building my dream home. Yes, I believe this will be my forever home. Yes, I’m putting everything I want for my family into this new residence. But, I also have to consider the “what ifs” of reselling the place. That type of forethought should always linger somewhere in your mind as you design your one-of-a-kind space. In today’s reel I juxtapose my plans with considerations of another owner, should I ever decide to sell. I think either will work out very well!
.

Question (and be honest): how many of you spend your holidays planning out the next year? This is pretty much me every year around the month of December. I love preparing for the season of trade shows and professional travel plans on my agenda for the first quarter of the new year. Planning my life out is so therapeutic for me; I absolutely have to able to see on paper the important aspects of what I’m supposed to be doing. I’ve coordinated all of my thoughts and itineraries with my au pair, kids and my significant other. Doing so helps me better ensure we all work in tandem to achieve all our goals as a family. Let’s go, 2023! 
.
.
.
.

With just 20 days left in the year, everything seems to be moving in fast-forward. Am I the only one who feels that way? I’m working on several big projects (I hinted at one this week, did you catch it?) I just surpassed 150k miles flown this year, and I even have some TV projects in the works (catch me on Property Brothers: Brother vs. Brother in January!). In short, there is LOT going on! Through it all, I’m trying to remember to be deliberate about taking time to simply…be. If we don’t, life will pass us by. There will never be another today, so take advantage of it!

Now that I’m moving, I’m starting to pay more attention to all of the little things that made this house my “home.” The artwork above my bed in this photo was the first thing I put my eyes on when I woke up every morning. These are my “ladies,” and I appreciate them so much. This Arthur Reese print gave me so much inspiration to start each day ready for whatever race was before me. I’m going to miss seeing this. Because I know the artwork may not be something the next owners appreciate, I’m interested to see what they will do differently in this space. Change is inevitable and sometimes difficult, but it always brings new perspectives and creativity. I look forward to that in the next chapter.
.

So, what are you getting yourself for Christmas this year? No one ever asks *that* question, do they? Most of us are so busy buying gifts for others that we don’t tend to think about the items we need. Well, allow me to help! Have you checked out @sunsetwestusa? The outdoor furnishings are made by hand with materials sourced from all over the world. With performance fabrics made to be durable and easy to clean, you’ll never worry about the quality diminishing! The best gift you could give your home at this time of year is patio furniture! That’s not what you were expecting, is it? Think about it. It’s the end of the year and we’ve seen all the trends come and go. Gift yourself something that will continue to give. I find that people focus on the indoors but never splurge on their outdoor spaces. This is your sign to invest in your patio, deck or rooftop and order @sunsetwestusa patio furniture as a gift to yourself. Get ahead of the game and be prepared for the warmer temps that are right around the corner

When designing and building a home, I love the complete autonomy to create from scratch the small simplicities that will positively impact how people live on a daily basis. In my bathroom space, I wanted to make sure there were dedicated (and designated) nooks to store fragrant soaps and shower balms. My bath moments mean so much because they’re a time to enjoy quietude away from life’s complexities and chaos. Small, custom details like this allow the space to be functional for every day but also ready for a lavish reprieve at any time.

Interior design is personalized and intuitive – the same is true of @JennAir luxury appliances. Each element of a home should be carefully thought out and chosen,  especially the kitchen, the most beloved gathering spot. #JennAirPartner When I laid eyes on the limited edition Smoke & Brass range, I was immediately captivated by the undeniable beauty. This professional-style range speaks directly to my signature style with its gorgeous brass detailing and distressing done all by hand! @JennAir doesn’t just make appliances, they make art designed to be the focal point of any kitchen. This range is one of only 50 that will ever be made, making it a truly unparalleled creation. It simply doesn’t get any more magnificent than that! Check out @JennAir to find the piece that completes your kitchen!
#Ad #BoundByNothing #BreeganJane

By now you all know how I feel about tubs in showers. It’s a Breegan Jane signature! What’s the secret? Clawfoot tubs! The bottom of the claw “feet” adjust, allowing you to tilt the tub so it drains in one direction while your shower drains in an opposite direction. Yes, I may have frustrated a plumber or two (LOL), but it’s innovative and works like a charm! I love that my job allows me to push boundaries when it comes to maximizing small spaces—even bathrooms!
.
.
.
.

Estimates suggest that at least 200 million women and girls today are living with the effects of the harmful practice of female genital mutilation. This practice persists largely due to gender inequality and generations clinging to cultural beliefs and attitudes. I believe every child is inherently a gift, and that every child deserves to live a life free of this harmful practice. Join us in our mission of eliminating the root causes of FGM and child marriage in Kenya, and empowering women and girls by providing them with the tools and support they need to create the conditions for them to thrive in futures they design. I actually sponsor two kids in Lebanon, so it was really fun to try this new recipe from @WorldVisionUSA’s “In the Kitchen” series. This #Lebanese flatbread is quick, easy, and delicious! @strongwomenstrongworld #manoushe #worldrefugeeday #inthekitchen More great recipes from around the world at worldvision.org/recipes
 
Recipe:

Ingredients:
1 1/4 cups lukewarm water
1 teaspoon active dry yeast
3 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
1 tablespoon sugar
2 teaspoons salt
1 tablespoon vegetable oil
1/2 cup za’atar
1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil
Instructions:
In a small bowl, mix 1/4 cup water and yeast. Set aside 5 to 10 minutes until yeast foams.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, and salt.
Add yeast mixture, remaining water, and vegetable oil to flour mixture. Mix until combined, and knead 10 minutes until dough is soft and elastic.
Place dough in a lightly oiled bowl. Cover and let rise in a warm spot until doubled in size, 1.5 to 2 hours.
Punch down dough and divide into four to six balls; use extra flour, if needed. Cover and let rise for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 400 degrees, and place a baking stone or steel on the bottom rack. (An upside-down cookie sheet will do.)
Combine za’atar and the olive oil. Set aside.
On a floured surface, press each ball with your palm. Turn and flatten from the center to edge, adding extra flour as needed until each is 1/4 inch thick and about 8 inches across.
Spread za’atar on the dough, leaving a 1/2-inch edge.
Slide pieces onto the heated stone, and bake for 7 to 10 minutes until golden and bubbly. Serve warm, and enjoy!

To take in the Kenyan wildlife and scenery is to bear witness to the circle of life. There are majestic beasts—elephants, antelope and zebras, to name a few—who seem carefree and content. But they also have a harsh reality—that of being prey for unsuspecting predators—that also cannot be missed. My heart goes out to these innocent animals, who simply want to live the lives they’re meant to have. This principle is why I work tirelessly to #endFGM for so many young Kenyan girls. Yet, those hopes and dreams are taken away because of unnecessary traditions and rituals. I’ll do everything in my power to give them their dreams, futures and possibilities back…WITHOUT FGM!

As most people know by now, I love using stone in interior design. But before-and-after photos like these show the difference stone can make in a space like a kitchen. I know most homeowners would immediately go for a more traditional tile backsplash, but I have always been a proponent of replacing tile with a slab of stone. Not only is it visually delightful, but it also creates an easier-to-clean surface without grout lines where bits and pieces of food can get caught. What’s more, in an open space like this, the stone actually becomes a focal point, almost like artwork, and brings elements of nature to the presentation. If you look closely, you’ll also see complements of stone in the kitchen island. This brings the entire look together and gives the eye another place to focus. Stone definitely has an uncanny way of bringing a luxe aesthetic to any home interior, wouldn’t you agree?

I always say there are no hard-and-fast rules when it comes to interior design. However, there are some techniques that are true to form if you want certain aesthetics. For example, if you want an open and serene vibe in a particular home space, you want to keep your decor light, bright, and as close to white as possible. Bright tones in a space really help to make the room look more expansive and breathable. And, the neutral layout is timeless, so your decor won’t date itself as easily. The versatility allows more flexible design coordination, so you’ll have more opportunities to switch out your decor, even with pops of color! I challenge anyone who thinks neutral color palettes are boring. Quite the opposite! They allow the most exciting design options available!

There’s this exclusive, special club that is pretty tough to get into. It’s where all the cool people are. It’s called the #boymom club, and I’ve been a member for a decade! LOL. I’m kidding, kind of. But really, boy moms… y’all okay? It’s tough out here trying to keep these little rascals alive when they insist on being daredevils almost daily! Being a mom to two little boys has been the most challenging and wild ride of my life… and I wouldn’t have it any other way! Share your tales with us in the comments if you can relate!

What’s the best way to add pizzazz to a space? Most people go directly to color. And to be fair, color DEFINITELY captures attention and draws the eye. However, it isn’t the only way! We all have such different tastes. Some people adore bright and colorful spaces. For others, lots of color can feel overwhelming. If you’re a neutrals person, but you’re craving a little “oomph” in your space. Think texture! I love combining different materials in a room. Velvet, woods, stone and metallics can all be found in neutral colors, but the differences in finishes is where the dynamism comes in. Try it out and let me know how you like it!

I don’t know if you can ever truly love yourself without first understanding yourself. I mean all the parts that make you who you are, the good, bad and ugly. We are complex beings with layers that sometimes no one ever sees. But, all of these things play a part in the development of who we become. I embrace all of it, allowing my lessons to guide me to higher versions of myself. Life is a winding road that leads us to mountain tops and valleys. There is greatness in both. Keep growing every day, but love today’s version of you as well.

Can you believe we are only 7 days away from Christmas? It feels like we were just discussing summer trends and back-to-school for the kids! This year has truly flown by, and while we have so much to be thankful for, it’s okay to give yourself a moment to catch your breath if you’re feeling a bit overwhelmed. Sometimes these transitions, like leaving one year behind and embarking on all that a new one has to offer, can be anxiety inducing. I can tell you that you’re not alone. But listen, great things are in store! I’m taking everything in—the lights and tree decorations, the music and ugly sweaters, and especially the festive mood everyone seems to be in. The time spent with others is my favorite part of this season. Amid all the work going on, it’s what I’m most focused on. What about you?

Sometimes the best ideas are some of the easiest. I always get a kick out of DIY projects that look super amazing…but when you get a chance to peek behind the curtain, it’s so simple! I think that’s a sign of a design genius! This DIYer certainly gets added to that group in my book. Who would have thought? Two materials, some paint, and a gorgeous new piece of decor is made. Check this out and let me know what YOU think!
.

“Worry never robs tomorrow of its sorrow, it only saps today of its joy.” — Leo F. Buscaglia

Quick check in with all my internet friends and fam! How are you guys doing? Life is “lifing” for us all, but I’m coming to you on this beautiful Tuesday with a reminder that worry doesn’t actually solve anything. It just makes you less focused on all the things that matter! If whatever you’re fretting about today won’t count in five years, I challenge you to let it go! Let’s finish the year with strength and joy. Give me some of your good news in the comments!

I firmly believe a home should be designed to fit the needs of the homeowner, which is why I’m installing a bit of an avant-garde primary closet in my bedroom. The layout will be more of a room, but with numerous clothing and accessory options needed for media appearances, the square footage is necessary. Plus, it will be positioned directly beside my video room for easy access and outfit changing. And, because I never stop being a mom, I have a special door catered to my children’s needs while recording. Check out today’s photo to see the details!

Want impactful decor? Be sure to select pieces that are properly proportioned to the space. Artwork that is too big or small for a wall can throw the balance off. Likewise, hanging it too high will give the room an unfinished look. Adorning walls is a part of interior design and decorating that many struggle to get right, but I’m equipped with all the tips you need! Contact me to schedule a virtual consultation! I’ll look at your space and help you achieve your design goals. Can’t wait to hear from you!

One of the things I love about design is the ability to fix common problems with clever solutions. Giving kids activities to do is useless if they’re unable to access them. On this @hgtv Extreme Makeover: Home Edition episode we opened up the room and found cute ways to install play areas and desks for the kids that fold up neatly when not in use! It’s functionality and innovative thinking at its best, and this #emhe family loved it!

“Children are the living messages we send to a time we will not see.” —John F. Kennedy

If there is any truth to Kennedy’s quote, we parents have a big responsibility. At a time of the year when society can try to fill our kids’ lives with desires for material goods, be sure to tell your kids what truly matters during this season: generosity, family, sharing with and caring for others, and so much more. These ideals are needed now, but they will be much more important in the future. Parents, take some time to remind your littles about these values.

Conversations around homeschooling always seem to turn controversial for some reason. But I have never regretted my decision to enroll my boys in their homeschool hybrid system. They have active social lives (their calendars rivel MINE!), classes that run the gamut, and sports and extracurricular activities galore! Their school and schedules allow us to maximize the time we spend together. For me, that’s priceless.

They say the only reason you should look back is to see how far you’ve come. My two boys have grown so much, literally and figuratively, in the last year, and I can’t help but think about them being knee-high and needing mom for everything. Now, they’re little men who have their own passions, goals and dreams. Even their Christmas wish lists have matured! Looking back for me, when it comes to them, means reminiscing on toy-filled holidays. But it also makes me look toward the future, which I know will be extremely merry and bright with these wide-eyed gentlemen in it.

Have you been naughty or nice? Maybe a bit of both? Either way, tomorrow is the day that so many little children wait for alllll year! Whether you’re a believer of the holiday or not, you’ve gotta admit, there’s something so sweet about seeing the kids’ eyes light up on Christmas morning. Even if presents aren’t your thing, I sincerely hope you have plans to either surround yourself with people who love you much, or spend a quiet day doing only the things you want! Hope this spread a little cheer down your timeline! Merry Christmas Eve!

MERRY CHRISTMAS, EVERYONE!! From our home to yours, I hope your day is filled with warmth and cheer! I plan on spending the day appreciating the best gift I could have ever received in life: my family. How are you spending yours? I’d love to hear about it in the comments!

I always say you should fashion your home based on the function it needs to serve for you and your family. So if you homeschool your kids and need space, that empty garage might be just the square footage you need! I love what this DIYer did with their space. It’s a perfect conversion!  Need help transforming a room in your home? I’m here! Let’s connect via @theexpert and find the perfect area to transition for your needs!

We are only one day post Christmas, and I’m already dreaming of somewhere tropical and warm! I never go too long without a visit to my favorite places on Earth. I wonder if another trip could be in the very near future? I guess we’ll have to wait and see! ‘Til then, I can feel those teal waters calling my name! Am I the only one who immediately starts craving a vacation after the holidays?

My family’s new beach home is shaping up to be the forever home we all wanted and dreamed of! When it comes to the kitchen, we’ll have all we need to make it the communal gathering space within the home. However, I also chose appliances that will help us live healthier lifestyles. Check out my plan in today’s reel. I couldn’t tell what my boys thought by their reactions; could you?

“At first glance it may appear too hard. Look again. Always look again.” - Maryanne Rodmacher

Newness is in the air! The end of the year always brings about thoughts of what the next year might hold. People are generally hopeful and excited for fresh adventures and endeavors. If there’s something you’ve been waiting to try or do, this is the time! Don’t let fear or anxious thoughts stop you from living the life you deserve. You can do hard things. You’re built for it. I’m optimistic about the year ahead. Great things are in store. What are you looking forward to?

I wholeheartedly believe there is no greater good to society than service to others, and I saw so much of that as a designer on @hgtv’s “Extreme Makeover: Home Edition.” I met so many giving families, but the impact the Fifita family had on their community was very evident in the lives of those they helped. I wanted to do something super special for their family, and I think they really enjoyed the final presentation. Check out today’s reel to see the highlights of the project.

In my experience, there are two schools of thought regarding this time of year. Either you’re full of hope for what the new year has and excited to ring in 2024, OR you’re dreading the end to a long vacation because you know it means a return to work and the chaos of life. I’m probably the weird one who loves the hustle and bustle that comes with work, because I thrive when things are busy. It helps that I have some amazing products coming to market soon that I get to share with you in the new year! Either way, I hope you’re enjoying the “now” and embracing the “soon-to-be.” The countdown begins!

So what if no one’s ever danced on their kitchen island? There’s a first time for everything! The beach home I’m building will be our family’s forever home, and we’re a music-loving, body-moving kind of crew! One of our islands will double as a dancefloor, complete with disco balls! Here’s how it will work. We can’t wait!

No one loves and supports kids like their parents. NO one. Sometimes, though, you come across people who, even in business, appreciate the “kid-ness” in kids. And, they’ll take the time to cultivate a child’s wonder, interest and curiosity, if but only for a moment. This photo is precious to me because it highlights a possible passion my oldest may develop. What it doesn’t show, though, is the amazing photographer who indulged my son by allowing him to hold and investigate the camera. Thank you, @jay.ibiza.photographer for having an open mind and heart toward my son during our photo shoot. I think you just may have lit a spark in an inquiring mind!

I adore traveling. It’s been a favorite pastime for decades. Having a career that requires visiting places around the world and country makes me love my job even more! Ironically, my love for it has grown since I had kids. That may sound weird coming from a parent, but I have two boys who not only love to travel but are great at it! They’re practically professionals at navigating airports and planes, and it makes traveling so easy for me. Seeing the world is now a family affair, and I’m looking forward to all the places we’ll get to see in 2024!

One of the best parts about watching kids grow up is realizing there is always more than meets the eye. When your kids are young, you notice every little detail about them almost right away. You see the variations in their eye color, the curl pattern in their hair, and the way their tiny feet are shaped. You might also take notice of little indicators of personality traits, sure of your guesses about them being shy or outgoing, boisterous or observant. But the truth is, you never quite have it all figured out. At each stage of development our kids reveal new talents, characteristics and skills. It’s like peeling back the layers of a never-ending onion. I’m having a blast watching my boys surprise me at each turn. What about you?

“If we all could see the world through the eyes of a child, we would see the magic in everything.” - Chee Vai Tang

Each time I take a moment to watch my boys have a new experience, visit a new place, or just simply get the giggles at the same time, I am reminded of how simple, yet magical the world can be. Children have a way of finding the *joy* in enjoyment that we adults often forget exists. I hope to move through life with more of that sparkle and wonder this year. Kids can teach us a lot about living life to the fullest, and that’s always my goal.

As a born-and-raised beach girl, there are a few things that I’ll always be a sucker for: warm weather, gorgeous sunrays, and an ocean view. That said, there’s no wonder why THIS homeowner’s view took my breath away! I’m building my dream home, but if I could build a second, it would totally have this view. What do you think? Could you live here? My answer: ABSOLUTELY!!

When are you happiest? I find that in this social media age of perfect photos and unrealistically beautiful vacation imagery, everyone believes they need a fantasy to be happy. It’s as if happiness can only be achieved if one is seated on the beach of a tropical island with mai tai in hand. Now listen, does that sound amazing? Yes. But most of us can’t whisk away to our dream destinations anytime we prefer. Does that mean limited opportunities for happiness? Absolutely not. Instead, we should focus on all the small moments we’re granted to laugh and smile and be content with the lives we get to live. Gratitude goes a long way as an attitude adjuster, and I don’t know about you, but I’m feeling pretty grateful right now. Here’s to finding our happy this year in big AND small ways.

One of the spaces I think my boys are most excited about is the DJ space. It’s been a passion of mine for decades, and now my boys have taken the baton and learned to curate music playlists. I have to say, they’re pretty good, too! But when I asked my son about his services, well…let’s just say I don’t get any special Mom privileges! 😂

Are you a journey or destination kind of person? I mean, when you are working towards something you feel passionately about, do you enjoy the process and work of making the dream come true, or are you much more satisfied once it’s all said and done? I love the process! Now, don’t get me wrong. When it comes to things like building my beach house, for instance, get it done! But, developing products and pouring my creative energy into things that I know my audience and client base will love? Well that’s top tier for me! Work is rewarding when I believe in what I’m doing, and I’m working on something really special right now that I can’t wait to reveal! Stay tuned!

This is the year of doing *all* the things. I’m not talking about New Year's resolutions. I’m talking about finding the gumption, the courage, the confidence to live your best life, on your terms. Whether you have a goal of starting a business, traveling more or even just making your bed everyday, this is the year to do it. Our kids are watching us make life decisions every day, and we indirectly model for them what’s possible. Life will never be perfect, but we can take advantage of each day to the best of our ability, in hopes of showing our children that life is worth living. Go after the dreams you have. Take a small step in that direction today and watch things begin to fall into place.

Do you ever get an idea in your head that you just can’t shake? It happens a lot when I’m designing. I’ll see something in my mind’s eye, and my determination to see it actualized is unmatched! If I can’t find what I need, I’ll design it! I think I’ve always been a product designer at heart, even from the time I was a little girl. Now, I relish the chance to bring custom, one-of-a-kind pieces to my clients to add an even more luxurious touch to their spaces. I enjoyed designing this custom tub and these sinks for this estate.
